<subSubSection id="F5E44EDE3F752711D6865884CAC65FEB" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph id="BD411D553F752712D6865884CA8A5C92" blockId="1.[151,1436,1352,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F752712D6865884CA015CDD" bold="true" box="[199,338,1422,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F752712D71B5884CA825CDD" box="[346,465,1422,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Body color</emphasis>
. Dark brown with brown and dark brown patches (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D2425884CF365CDD" box="[1027,1125,1422,1445]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Figs 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D27D5884CF365CDD" box="[1084,1125,1422,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Costal margin of forewing (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D6DE58BACBB25CBF" box="[159,225,1456,1479]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D69258BACBB25CBF" box="[211,225,1456,1479]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) with a black spot in distal 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D45958BAC9705CBF" box="[536,547,1456,1479]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D46F58BAC96E5CBF" box="[558,573,1456,1479]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="3.0">3</number>
. Face (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D4CC58BAC99D5CBF" box="[653,718,1456,1479]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D48058BAC99D5CBF" box="[705,718,1456,1479]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown with yellow spots and short transverse band. Vertex with brown median transverse line.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD411D553F752712D68658FCCA685FEF" blockId="1.[151,1436,1352,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F752712D68658FCCA1A5F75" box="[199,329,1526,1549]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Morphology</emphasis>
. Head (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D7E758FCCABB5F75" box="[422,488,1526,1549]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D79D58FCCABB5F75" box="[476,488,1526,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) including eyes slightly narrower than pronotum; fore margin (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D2F758FCCE6B5F75" box="[1206,1336,1526,1549]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Figs 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D2B158FCCE6B5F75" box="[1264,1336,1526,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.7" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="1.0">1–2, 4</number>
</figureCitation>
) slightly produced anteriorly with two transverse striations; crown with midlength approximately 1.5 times as long as next to eyes. Ocelli (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D6A95B31CA195F2A" box="[232,330,1595,1618]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Figs 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D7605B31CA195F2A" box="[289,330,1595,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
</figureCitation>
) situated on fore margin of vertex, not visible in dorsal view, its diameter equal to distance between ocellus to adjacent eye. Clypellus (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D44A5B54C9195F0D" box="[523,586,1630,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D47C5B54C9195F0D" box="[573,586,1630,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) slightly broad at base, expanding apically; antennal (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D2CA5B54CF995F0D" box="[1163,1226,1630,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,202,963]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1398,194,974]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, face; 4. ♂, head in anterior view; 5. Forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259705/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D2FC5B54CF995F0D" box="[1213,1226,1630,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) bases located near middle of eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD411D553F752712D6865BA9CFA65F87" blockId="1.[151,1436,1352,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Profemur (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D77D5BA9CAD85FC2" box="[316,395,1699,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D7315BA9CAD85FC2" box="[368,395,1699,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) IC row with long fine setae; AV row with about 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D5F35BA9C89E5FC2" box="[946,973,1699,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="10.0">10</number>
stout and short setae; AM 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D2B55BA9CFAE5FC2" box="[1268,1277,1699,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
with only one strong and long seta; fore tibia with dorsal setal formula 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D4AC5BCCC9A45FA5" box="[749,759,1734,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D54A5BCCC8495FA5" box="[779,794,1734,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="5.0">5</number>
. 
<collectingCountry id="C5E95DC53F752712D5655BCCC80A5FA5" box="[804,857,1734,1757]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D58B5BCCC8B75FA5" box="[970,996,1734,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="11.0">11</number>
setae of AV row, 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D2DE5BCCCFE95FA5" box="[1183,1210,1734,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="19.0">19</number>
setae of AD row, PV row and AV row with numerous setae; first tarsomere with five platellae and second tarsomere with four.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD411D553F752712D6865A01C9355E8A" blockId="1.[151,1436,1352,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="8F8AC1473F752712D6865A01CA345E5A" box="[199,359,1803,1826]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Male pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D4195A01C9CF5E5A" box="[600,668,1803,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D4CF5A01C9CF5E5A" box="[654,668,1803,1826]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) dorsal margin sinuated; caudodorsal part elongated, distal half with numerous long macrosetae. Valve (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D4575A24C9045E3D" box="[534,599,1838,1861]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D4085A24C9045E3D" box="[585,599,1838,1861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) short, bandlike, anterior margin sinuated. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D2B15A24CE615E3D" box="[1264,1330,1838,1861]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D3655A24CE615E3D" box="[1316,1330,1838,1861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad at basal 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D6995A5ACBB15E1F" box="[216,226,1872,1895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="0B360F723F752712D6AD5A5ACBAF5E1F" box="[236,252,1872,1895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="4.0">4</number>
, then gradually tapered to elongate subacute apex and fingerlike. Style (
<figureCitation id="25C501D03F752712D2635A5ACF375E1F" box="[1058,1124,1872,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
